        <num>20-2-1090</num>
        <content>
          <p>The various school boards of the counties, cities, and independent school systems employing school buses are authorized and required to cause policies of insurance to be issued insuring the school children riding therein to and from school against bodily injury or death at any time resulting from an accident or collision in which such buses are involved. The amount of such insurance shall be within the discretion of the respective boards.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1949, p. 1155, ยง 1.)</p>
